OL,6,FLawyers for the department said Mr
OL,7,FChalk believed Brown "would pose a
OL,8,Fsignificant risk of serious harm to
OL,9,Fthe public if released on licence",
OL,10,Fadding that the offender had
OL,11,F"persistently refused to engage in the
OL,12,Frehabilitative elements of his
OL,13,Fsentence".
OL,15,FMr Chalk's referral, enabled through a
OL,16,F"power to detain" provision introduced
OL,17,Fthrough the Police, Crime, Sentencing
OL,18,Fand Courts Act 2022, overrode Brown's
OL,19,Fautomatic release.
